===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{Han compound|黍|利|c1=s|c2=p|t1=millet|ls=psc}}; however, the semantic component is contracted. A regularized but unused variant is [[㴝]], while a variant without contraction is [[𥣥]].

===Etymology===
; “black; numerous”
: Cognate with {{zh-l|*黧|black}} ({{zh-ref|Wang, 1982}}). Note similarities to {{cog|my|ရီ|t=dim, dusky, dizzy}}.
; “Li people”
: From {{bor|zh|lic|Hlai}}. Alleged to be used in Eastern Han dynasty book {{w|Yiwu Zhi}}:
:: {{zh-x|《^南裔 ^異物 ^志》謂：^俚 在 ^廣州 之 南，俗 呼 ^俚 為 黎\^𥠖{lí}。|ref=顧炎武《天下郡國利病書》, early Qing dynasty|''The Records of Foreign Matters'' says that the Li people live in the south of Guangzhou, and it is commonly known as "'''𥠖'''" (Li)}}
: Before Song dynasty, {{zh-l|俚}} was a more common term.

